SIMPLE: lithotype
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lithotype
<hw>Lith"o*type</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
etched stone surface for printing, having the design in relief; also,
the process of printing from such a surface, or that which is printed
from it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A machine, with a keyboard like that of a
typewriter, for making a lithographic transfer sheet. It produces a
perforated strip of paper which controls the printing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lithotype</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Lithotype
<hw>Lith"o*type</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Lithotyped</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Lithotyping</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To prepare for
printing with plates made by the process of lithotypy. See
<er>Lithotypy</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lithotypic</ent>⟦br⟧
